  "title": "Video generation now supports A-to-B transitions",
  "summary": "Video transitions, audio speaker diarization, and a massive wave of thirty new community apps hitting the greenhouse.\n\nYou can now pass a positional image array to the video endpoints (image[0] for the start frame, image[1] for the end frame) and let models like seedance, veo, and wan-fast hallucinate the in-between. Full support is already rolled out across the API, SDK, CLI, and MCP tools.\n\nThe `/v1/audio/transcriptions` endpoint now accepts `response_format=diarized_json`. It returns OpenAI-compatible segments with speaker labels, powered by AssemblyAI and ElevenLabs Scribe. You can finally stop guessing who is talking in your hour-long meeting recordings.\n\nThe community shipped some serious infrastructure today. AI Clip Finder uses FastAPI and LLMs to automatically extract social-ready clips from long videos. Meanwhile, AI Image Studio and Lunere Image Gen both dropped full-pipeline workbenches for generating and refining images via the REST API.",
